body: Sample Call: Caller stated that they were a freshman and having a hard time adjusting to college life. Caller also stated that it may be related to their depression and anxiety. Caller has a difficult time making friends and doesn't know how to start talking to people. Scared that they may look silly or mess up.
couns_opinion: This felt like a very positive call. I feel like it really helped them to vent

body: Sample Call: Caller is a freshman. She talked about how she was a finance major, but wanted to switch to communications. She is not happy with finance and stated that she is really struggling. She feels that math has never been her thing, and she only chose this major because her dad thought she should. She has some friends who introduced her to communications. She has always loved stuff like that and took a couple classes this term to see how she liked it. She called her parents to tell them that she would like to switch her major. Her parents weren't happy though and they pay for her tuition. They said that if she switches her major that they will not longer pay for her. She kept talking and going in circles. Eventually she decided that she was going to talk to her parents again and explain all the career opportunities, and show that this is a good career path for her. She thanked the primary counselor for listening to her, and hung up.

Sample Call: Caller said that she has called before and that she found it very helpful last time so she wanted to try the helpline again. Primary said that they were glad that this resource has been beneficial for her. Caller went on to talk about how she and her girlfriend of 5 months broke up last week. She has been having a hard time with coping the past week. She really liked her, but they argued a lot. They have both been very stressed and decided to take a break. Today she saw a photo online of her ex and another girl holding hands. The caller began to cry. Primary let her know that they were listening and that she can take a minute to herself and is here whenever she is ready. Caller began to talk about all the times they fought and the good times as well. This was the callers second serious relationship. After talking for a while, the caller said that she was really tired and should just get some sleep. The primary reminded her of the hours, and also asked if she wanted the number to the counseling center. The caller said that she could just look it up online if she wanted to. Then the call ended.
couns_opinion: I struggled not to circle with this caller. As a repeat caller, it was difficult to approach the same issues over and over without it going into circling.
Caller was looking for any online counseling service.

body: Caller was anxious and stressed. Caller stated that she was scared of her roommate. She explained that they fight all the time and her RA won't do anything because her RA and the roommate are good friends and are from the same hometown. Caller doesn't know what to do and had to hang up at one point during the call because her roommate walked into the room.
referrals: Counseling Center,9-1-1/DUPD/Public Safety,7 Cups of Tea,Housing/Residential Living,Resident Director/Resident Assistant

body: Caller said that they had taken some substances at a party and was scared and unsure about what to do. Counselor asked if the caller felt they needed a doctor and they said yes.
couns_opinion: I was unsure on whether or not to default to the on-call for this one
